0.body: I'm a software engineer, leaving in France. I've been programming since 2014. Main techs : cpp c Confident : lua opengl qt unreal unity csharp Currently learning : python rust vulkan Already used : blender javascript typescript html css php swift asm github https://github.com/rhoffsch42 youtube https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCgjzbalQP2kbW4fsJ14_ftQ mail rhoffsch@gmail.com
0.title: Welcome

1.body: Side projects My first Unreal Engine project, currently Blueprint-only. I chose to make a Gradius-like to get my hands on the engine. This is a technical demo, levels are intentionnally short and easy. Details All of this work was done myself, no plug-in were used for the gameplay. Only 3D models, images and audio were imported. What I learned to use during this project: Levels/Scenes, GameInstance and GameMode, Input modes, Actor and ActorComponents, Projectile Component, Function and Macro Library, SaveGame, Key bindings, Event calls and bindings, collision presets, UI Widgets, UI Animation, Materials, NiagaraSystem, Damage system and more... Download (Windows) ⇗ cpp
1.breadcrumbs: Side projects » unreal cpp Arcade Game inspired from Gradius
1.title: unreal cpp Arcade Game inspired from Gradius
